title: ‘Abso-f*****g-lutely’: Jon Stewart calls on Bill and Hillary Clinton to comply with Epstein subpoena
description: ‘The Daily Show’ host Jon Stewart has called on former US President Bill Clinton and former Secretary of state Hillary Clinton to comply with their congressional subpoena.  On his podcast, Stewart answered a question on whether the former president and former first lady should comply with the House Oversight Committee’s investigation into Jeffrey Epstein.  The two are refusing to testify in the Epstein trial, defying subpoenas to appear before the committee this week.  Stewart, despite calling for them to comply, questioned why they should if the Department of Justice was “not complying with releasing the files”.

title: Pentagon contractor investigated after leaking classified information to the press
description: White House Press Secretary Karoline Leavitt criticises a Pentagon contractor for leaking classified information to the Washington Post.  “The individual, unfortunately, a contractor at the Pentagon, chose to unlawfully leak classified and very serious information to this Washington Post reporter,” Ms Leavitt said.  “The administration is not going to tolerate leaks, especially from within the national security apparatus of the United States government.  “If you break the law and if you endanger our men and women in uniform, you are going to be held accountable, period.”

title: Tim Walz blasted over latest plea to ‘turn the temperature down’ following anti-ICE protests
description: Governor Tim Walz has been widely criticised following his latest plea to "turn the temperature down" in an address to Minnesotans.  In Walz's "direct appeal" to the US President, the governor pleaded that Donald Trump "stop this campaign of retribution."  Governor Walz's post has since been blasted by social media users, with many accusing him of inciting the growing anti-ICE violence in his state.  "You've spent the entire 2026 year so far saying your state is 'at war' with the federal government," wrote one user.  "You are quite literally fanning the flames of chaos."

title: Minneapolis mayor shifts rhetoric and sends ultimatum to anti-ICE protesters
description: Minneapolis Mayor Jacob Frey has shifted his tone, calling for peace across his city following a week of ICE protests.  Since the death of an American woman in Minneapolis at the hands of an ICE agent, many people have protested ICE and Donald Trump’s administration.  ICE has continued to conduct raids within the state of Minnesota, much to the disapproval of its Governor Tim Walz and Minneapolis Mayor Jacob Frey.  Frey had previously told ICE to “get the f**k” out of his city, following the death of Renee Good by the agent.  During a news conference on Wednesday, Frey softened his tone and called for “peace” in the state of Minnesota.  “I’m calling for peace, everybody has a role in achieving that peace, and we’re going to try and do everything we can to keep it,” Frey said.

title: ‘Problem from the outset’: Labor's hate speech bill should 'not be passed in its current form’
description: Former Home Affairs secretary Mike Pezzullo scrutinises the hate speech bill and believes it should not be passed in its current form.  “Not in its current form,” Mr Pezzullo told Sky News Australia.  “Unless you get the law precise enough that it can then be translated into the materials that the officials, the investigators, the prosecutors are going to be able to act upon, you’ve got a problem from the outset.   “Hatred is a very nebulous concept to try to capture.”

title: eSafety Commissioner open to facing US Congress
description: eSafety Commissioner Julie Inman Grant has not ruled out travelling to the US to testify before a Congressional committee.  The group, chaired by Republican Jim Jordan, wants her to give evidence in relation to Australia's Online Safety Act.   There is concern Australia's enforcement of the law threatens the free speech of Americans.  Ms Inman Grant says she has been in contact with the Congressman but believes she may not be the right person to give evidence.

title: Albanese praises social media ban for under-16s
description: Prime Minister Anthony Albanese reveals 4.7 million social media accounts have been deactivated since Australia’s under-16 ban.

title: PM says dealing with Coalition is like ‘trying to grab smoke’
description: Prime Minister Anthony Albanese describes trying to get an arrangement with the Coalition as “trying to grab smoke”.  “They sat back last year and didn't engage at all on environmental laws,” Mr Albanese said.    “If you can let me know what they’re prepared to vote for … because at the moment I'm not sure what it is.”  “I don't think they know either.”

title: Megyn Kelly unleashes on CBS rebranded lineup amid networks continued ratings disaster
description: Commentator Megyn Kelly has unleashed on CBS’s rebrand under new editor in chief Bari Weiss, mocking their new lineup and continued ratings disaster.

title: ‘Horrible’: McIntosh calls for Grok to be removed after creating ‘abhorrent’ nude content
description: Shadow Communications Minister Melissa McIntosh in disbelief that Elon Musk’s AI creation app Grok has the capabilities to create explicit images.  “It’s absolutely unacceptable that nude images could be created of an individual … without their consent,” Ms McIntosh told Sky News Australia.  “Everything should be thrown at this issue.  “It’s abhorrent, it’s horrible stuff.”

title: Whoopi Goldberg goes on unhinged rant over FBI search of reporter's house linked to leaker
description: 'The View' co-host Whoopi Goldberg has gone on a rant about the FBI searching a Washington Post reporter's home.  The search was part of a probe into a government contractor accused of illegally leaking classified material to the press.  The search warrant executed by law enforcement seemed to confuse Goldberg as she continued to question the move.  US Presidnet Donald Trump has announced the leaker has already been detained by law enforcement.  White House Press Secretary commented further on the leaker during a press briefing.

title: Federal judge savages Gavin Newsom and Democrats for California redistricting
description: Federal judge Kenneth Lee has unleashed on California Governor Gavin Newsom and Democrats following a voter-approved congressional map district redraw.  The redistricting was to combat similar redistricting in Texas, which would give the GOP an advantage, and was backed by US President Donald Trump.  According to the judge, California’s redraw favours Democrats and has labelled it a case of “racial gerrymandering”.  A three-judge panel saw a 2-1 ruling in favour of the voter-approved districting and denied requests from state Republicans.  “California sullied its hands with this sordid business when it engaged in racial gerrymandering as part of its mid-decade congressional redistricting plan to add five more Democratic House seats,” Lee exclaimed.

title: ‘What changes are they for?’: Albanese responds to Greens and Libs opposing hate speech bill
description: Prime Minister Anthony Albanese says the government is still open to other ideas on hate speech laws, in response to the Greens and Liberal Party expressing serious concerns.  Mr Albanese criticises the Coalition for not putting forward a “single proposed change”.  “They have had people going out there saying they would oppose these laws before they had even read them.  “What changes are they for?”

title: ‘Not a great look’: Kamala Harris buys $8 million Malibu dream house
description: Former US vice president Kamala Harris and her husband Doug Emhoff have recently bought a new Malibu mansion with an eyewatering price tag of over $US8 million.  The house is a 4,000-square-foot home with four bedrooms and six bathrooms in the prominent Point Dume neighbourhood.  According to the online listing, the 1979 house "is bathed in natural light, featuring high wood-beamed ceilings, a built-in speaker system, and a gas fireplace."  Fox News host Jesse Waters weighed in and blasted the failed presidential hopeful's tasteless purchase.  Waters goes on to lash Harris for "squandering" billions of dollars of donor money for her campaign and not winning.  The Fox News host finishes by calling her memoir a "gossip book" and saying the purchase is not a great look.

title: Lindsey Graham urges Donald Trump to take ‘bigger’ action against Iran to topple regime
description: Republican Senator Lindsey Graham has urged US President Donald Trump to take strong military action against Iran and topple the regime.  On Thursday, Graham dispelled rumours about President Trump's "resolve" on attacking Iran as "not accurate".  The Republican Senator revealed Trump is weighing up whether an operation against Iran should be "bigger or smaller", with Graham opting for the "bigger".  "There are a lot of headlines out there that are, in my view, not accurate. President Trump's resolve is not the question: Question is, when we do an operation like this, should it be bigger or smaller? I'm in the camp of bigger," Graham said.  "Time will tell. I'm hopeful and optimistic that the regime's days are numbered."
